HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 128
By Howell
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Lois Johnson Bates of
Benton.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Lois Johnson Bates; and
WHEREAS, Lois Bates was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for her fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, Lois Bates was born on February 7, 1925, in Varnell, Georgia, to John H.
and Edna Johnson; she grew up in Conasauga, Tennessee, and graduated from Polk County
High School in 1943; and
WHEREAS, after high school, Ms. Bates began working in Oak Ridge at Carbide and
Carbon Chemical Corporation until World War II ended in 1947; in 1962, she graduated from
nursing school conducted by Bradley County Board of Education and the Tennessee State of
Vocational Board of Education; and
WHEREAS, for approximately forty years, Lois Bates served with the utmost acumen
and alacrity as a nurse at Bradley Memorial Hospital, Cleveland Community Hospital, and
Benton Family Healthcare Center, devoting herself fully to caring for each and every patient;
and
WHEREAS, a dedicated volunteer, Ms. Bates was called to help underserved
communities, and she was proud to work with The Empty Stocking Fund, an organization
founded to serve underprivileged children, for over thirty years; she also volunteered with the
Meals on Wheels Program; and
